<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,976,1174]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="140">1. Tegminae not exceeding the first abdominal tergite. The penultimate abdominal tergite of the male with normal development, not prolonged. Male subgenital plate notch as deep as a quarter of the length of the subgenital plate.................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,976,1174]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
- Tegminae surpasses the first abdominal tergite, reaching about the middle of the abdomen. The penultimate tergite extends over the last abdominal tergite and is slightly divided at the apex. Male subgenital plate notch deep, reaching half the total length of the subgenital plate........................................................................... 
